<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/noty/3.1.4/noty.min.css" integrity="sha512-0p3K0H3S6Q4bEWZ/WmC94Tgit2ular2/n0ESdfEX8l172YyQj8re1Wu9s/HT9T/T2osUw5Gx/6pAZNk3UKbESw==" crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/noty/3.1.4/noty.min.js" integrity="sha512-lOrm9FgT1LKOJRUXF3tp6QaMorJftUjowOWiDcG5GFZ/q7ukof19V0HKx/GWzXCdt9zYju3/KhBNdCLzK8b90Q==" crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></script>
    
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/css/signup.css">
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>signup page</title>
</head>

<body>
    <div id="signupcontainer">
        <div id="signuptextcontainer">
            <div id="signuptext">
                <h1>Welcome to Codeial</h1>
                <span>
                    A habit tracker app is a digital tool designed to help users establish and maintain positive habits in their daily lives. These apps typically allow users to set specific goals or habits they want to cultivate, such as exercising regularly, drinking more water, reading, or meditating. Users can then track their progress over time, often through visual representations like calendars, graphs, or charts.
                </span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="signupform">
            <form action="/auth/signup" method="post">
                <h1>sign up</h1>
                <input type="text" placeholder="Username " id="name" name="name" required>
                <input type="email" placeholder="abc@gmail.com" id="email" name="email" required>
                <input type="password" placeholder="Password" id="password" name="password" required>
                <input type="password" placeholder="Confirm Password" id="confirm_password" name="confirm_password"
                    required>
                <input type="submit" id="formbutton" placeholder="signup">
                <a href="/auth/signinpage">Already have account</a>
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>